      "side": 1,
      "message": "Ah, right, so that reinforces the point for refactoring:\n\n- \u0027latest first\u0027 statement in documentation is not accurate, because\n- Revision gets its comparator from RevisionUnion, where\n- \u0027no revision\u0027 compares as less as any revision, hence\n- the natural order is null, 0000-00-00, ..., 9999-99-99\n\nHere the order is null, 9999-99-99, ...., 0000-00-00, which is neither natural or reverse order of Revision.\n\nNote that we have already have a well-established meaning of what \"newest revision first\" means here: https://github.com/opendaylight/yangtools/blob/8098f35c50fb4e3723b1936009ab334c2023d194/model/yang-model-api/src/main/java/org/opendaylight/yangtools/yang/model/api/SchemaContext.java#L54-L61 -- and it is the exact reverse of the natural order.\n\nSo that sheds a light on how the lookups through maps actually work. I will refactor that part first and circle back here afterwards.",
